MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/shells/pulse/.*(CastCard|DmHero|DmBioQuote|PlayerProfile).*\.tsx$
ADVISORY: |
  Pulse shell convention: there is NO `stereotype` field on SocialPlayer.

  The shell re-uses `player.bio` as a pseudo-stereotype, rendering it only when
  the bio is short enough to be a single line (roughly a label, not a paragraph):

    const stereotype = player.bio && player.bio.length > 4 && player.bio.length <= 50
      ? player.bio : '';

  If `bio` is long (real pre-game interview text), it's rendered elsewhere as a
  pull-quote (DmBioQuote only renders when bio.length > 50). The two surfaces
  never overlap.

  Wrong (TS2339 at build time):
    <div>{player.stereotype}</div>

  Right (match existing convention — see CastCard.tsx:25-27 and DmHero.tsx):
    const stereotype = player.bio && player.bio.length > 4 && player.bio.length <= 50
      ? player.bio : '';
    {stereotype && <div>{stereotype}</div>}

  Source of truth: packages/shared-types/src/index.ts:417 SocialPlayerSchema —
  only `id, personaName, avatarUrl, bio?, status, silver, gold, realUserId?,
  qaAnswers?` exist.
